<h1>Govspeak help</h1>
<div>
  <h2>Headers</h2>
<pre>## Top level heading
### Second level heading
#### Third level heading

Don't use a single #.
</pre>
  <h2>Text Styles</h2>
  <pre>**This text will be bold**
__This will also be bold__
</pre>
  <h2>Blockquotes</h2>
  <pre>As the P.M. said:

> Rule Britannia!
> Britannia rule the waves!</pre>
  <h2>Acronyms</h2>
  <pre>*[HMRC]: Her Majesty's Revenue and Customs</pre>
</div>

<div>
  <h2>Unordered List</h2>
  <pre>* item 1
* item 2
* subitem
* another subitem</pre>
  <h2>Ordered List</h2>
  <pre>1. item 1
2. item 2
3. item 3
 * subitem
 * another subitem</pre>
 <h2>Tables</h2>
 <pre>| name | colour |
|--------|-------|
| apple | green |
| banana | yellow |</pre>

  <h2>Images</h2>
  <p>First upload your image(s), then:</p>
  <pre>!!<em>n</em></pre>
  <p>e.g. for the first image:</p>
  <pre>!!1</pre>
</div>

<div>
  <h2>Internal links</h2>
  <pre>[link text](/government/admin/policies/3373 "Hover text goes here")
  </pre>
  <h2>External links</h2>
  <p>Links with external URLs will automatically display as external links.</p>
  <pre>[link text](http://www.example.com "Hover text goes here")</pre>
  <h2>Video links</h2>
  <p>Links to Youtube videos will automatically be displayed in an embedded media player.</p>
  <pre>[link text](youtube-video-url)</pre>
  <p>Use the title of the video for the "link text", e.g. :-</p>
  <pre>[The Queens Diamond Jubilee Concert](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OXHPWmnycno)</pre>

  <h2>Footnotes</h2>
  <pre>This is a text with a footnote[^1].

[^1]: And here is the definition.</pre>
</div>
